<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
Three specimens 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="3.0" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3-7 mm</quantity>
, CB; one specimen 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
, SRB.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
Feeds on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Decaisne" authorityYear="1841" class="Bryopsidophyceae" family="Halimedaceae" genus="Halimeda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Halimeda macroloba" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="macroloba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Halimeda macroloba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on which it is highly cryptic. Host and prey found in soft sediment habitats near coral reefs between 0.5 and 9 m depth. Multiple individuals may be found feeding on a single prey item. Populations of the host algae 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. macroloba" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="macroloba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">H. macroloba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been found at only two locations at the island, 6-9 m depth at SRB and a small intertidal patch at site CB at 0.5-1.5 m. The abundance of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" genus="E." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. pusilla" order="Sacoglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">E. pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found to be greater at CB than on the larger but less dense population of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. macroloba" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="macroloba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">H. macroloba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at site SRB.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Distribution.</paragraph>
