<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
The status of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bergh" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Gastropoda" family="Plakobranchidae" genus="Elysia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elysia pusilla" order="Sacoglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Elysia pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its taxonomic implications for the genus needs closer investigation (
<bibRefCitation author="Jensen, KR" journalOrPublisher="The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="207 - 223" refId="B121" refString="Jensen, KR, 2009. Sacoglossa (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Opisthobranchia) from Singapore. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement 22: 207 - 223" title="Sacoglossa (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Opisthobranchia) from Singapore." volume="22" year="2009">Jensen 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jensen, KR" journalOrPublisher="The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="226 - 249" refId="B122" refString="Jensen, KR, 2015. Sacoglossa (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Heterobranchia) from northern coasts of Singapore. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement 31: 226 - 249" title="Sacoglossa (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Heterobranchia) from northern coasts of Singapore." volume="31" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4148.1.1" author="Krug, P" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 137" refId="B140" refString="Krug, P, Vendetti, J, Valdes, A, 2016. Molecular and morphological systematics of Elysia Risso, 1818 (Heterobranchia: Sacoglossa) from the Caribbean region. Zootaxa 4148: 1 - 137, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4148.1.1" title="Molecular and morphological systematics of Elysia Risso, 1818 (Heterobranchia: Sacoglossa) from the Caribbean region." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4148.1.1" volume="4148" year="2016">Krug et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Recent observations carried out by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0215063" author="Mehrotra, R" journalOrPublisher="Marine Biodiversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" refId="B165" refString="Mehrotra, R, Monchanin, C, Scott, CM, Phongsuwan, N, Caballer Gutierrez, M, Chavanich, S, Hoeksema, BW, 2019. Selective consumption of sacoglossan sea slugs (Mollusca: Gastropoda) by scleractinian corals (Cnidaria: Anthozoa). PLoS ONE 14: e0215063. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0215063" title="Selective consumption of sacoglossan sea slugs (Mollusca: Gastropoda) by scleractinian corals (Cnidaria: Anthozoa). PLoS ONE 14: e 0215063." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0215063" year="2019">Mehrotra et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
indicate that 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" genus="E." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. pusilla" order="Sacoglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">E. pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens from Koh Tao are considered palatable to opportunistic scleractinian coral predators and are readily consumed by these reef building corals. However, to date, no instances of natural prey capture of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" genus="E." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. pusilla" order="Sacoglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">E. pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by these corals has been documented.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
